The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Three killed in road mishaps
                                                                                                               Three killed in road mishaps
                            
	Three men died in three mishaps in the city since Thursday night.        
	Asit Kumar Mullick, a 40-year-old CBI stenographer, was crushed by an oil tanker after he fell off his motorcycle on Taratala Road on Friday evening. Cops said Mullick, who was on his way to his Mahestala home, lost balance while trying to steer his bike past a pedestrian on a dark stretch between Taratala and Jinjira Bazaar.        
	Around 9.30pm on Thursday, Mohammad Ishaque, in his mid-40s, was hit by an unidentified vehicle on the EM Bypass-Beleghata Main Road crossing. He died around midnight at NRS Hospital.         
	Around 11pm on Thursday, a youth slipped and fell off the footboard of a private bus plying on route 3D/1 and was crushed under its wheels at Moulali crossing. He was declared dead at NRS Hospital.        
	All three drivers escaped.        
	Sewage plant: The first sewage treatment plant in the added areas of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation was inaugurated by mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharyya at Keorapukur in Behala on Friday. The Rs 13-crore plant is part of the Asian Development Bank-funded Calcutta Environment Improvement Project. It will treat 45 million litres of sewage per day and serve about 16sq km in east Behala, Garia and Tollygunge.        
	Set ablaze: A middle-aged woman and her three sons were arrested for allegedly setting her nephews wife on fire in their Sinthee home early on Friday. Sakuntala Singh and her sons Munna, Kanai and Shankar sprinkled kerosene on 28-year-old Soni Singh and set her ablaze over a family dispute, said cops. Soni was admitted to Medical College and Hospital with 80 per cent burns. Her husband Dharma Singh, a driver, also sustained burns while trying to save her.        
	Rape arrest: Hari Mitra, a 45-year-old rickshawvan puller, was arrested in Thakurpukur on Friday for allegedly raping his 14-year-old daughter. Haris 22-year-old son lodged a complaint against his father after the girl became pregnant.        
	Assault on tenants: A gang barged into a second-floor flat in a building adjacent to Beleghata police station on Friday afternoon and beat up 42-year-old resident Alok Sarkar and his wife Shyamali, allegedly to make them move out. Shibnath Gayen, 42, was arrested in connection with the assault. Residents of the buildings eight flats pay rent through the office of rent control.        
	Rail blockade: Nearly 1,000 truck drivers and helps blocked railway tracks for an hour on Friday morning after extortionists allegedly shot at a driver near Sodepur railway station on Thursday night. Sunil Singh, 45, who was hit by the bullet in the abdomen was admitted to hospital in a critical condition.                                                                                                                                                                            
